tweet: Excited my @Mizzou Tigers🐯 are playing in the #LibertyBowl today!  🏈Looking for a BIG WIN over Oklahoma State!  Go, Tigers!! 🐯🐯

In a world that often is full of bad news, it's refreshing to remember angels delivered a message of “Good News.” I’m so grateful for it. I hope you get to celebrate the birth of Jesus this Christmas with friends & family and experience His love & presence throughout the year. pic.twitter.com/be1CVY96SA

(2/2) I encourage Democrats to support legislation that funds our government & prioritizes our security by increasing funding to protect our border, stops flow of deadly drugs into our communities, & stems tide of illegal immigration. I stand by, ready to support such a measure.

(1/2) On December 20 I voted for a CR to fund entire govt through February 7, that included much needed border security funding for @DHSgov while also funding other select federal agencies. Unfortunately, the Senate did not reach the required sixty votes necessary to approve it.

Pleased to support the First Step Act that @POTUS just signed into law → this bill works to reduce recidivism and give certain non-violent prisoners a second chance when they reenter society. Great step in the right direction.

I fully support @SteveDaines call to fund government & #BuildTheWall by changing the unconstitutional 60-vote filibuster rule in the Senate. The American people gave us the Majority. We need to quit squandering this opportunity to fulfill their wishes. #MajorityRules

Pretty shot of Capitol I took tonight after voting to build the wall, provide disaster relief, and fund our government. We must stop the drug cartels from bringing drugs into our country which kill our kids. Calling on Senate to pass it tomorrow. #bordersecurity #stopdrugcartels pic.twitter.com/V8dZO7xmGu

.@POTUS continues his promise of supporting Missourians and agriculturalists across our country by signing the bipartisan #2018FarmBill into law today. Pics below of our signing the bill before it went to the President. pic.twitter.com/aax24HnQbX

Pleased that last night the House moved to authorize $20 million annually for Alzheimer’s research and prevention. Especially meaningful since my own mom passed away from Alzheimer’s complications in 2015.

Witnessed a great speech by a great American @speakerryan.  He reflected on accomplishments & challenged us to lift our gaze & tackle the challenges yet before us. I’m thankful I had the privilege of serving w/ him & wish he & his family well in next chpt of life.#farewelladdress pic.twitter.com/0RIQA31cUv

We need to #BuildTheWall!  I’ve visited the border & seen the danger. Cartels are bringing billions of $ of drugs across our open border which come to our communities & kill our kids. This must stop! #SafetyFirst #FundTheWall

I enjoyed making Christmas 🌲 sugar #cookies this afternoon with Tiffany!! Now it feels like #christmas! 🎅🏼We’re going to have fun sharing them with friends and family (& eating them!😉🍪#seasonofgiving pic.twitter.com/mpK64CB4F1

Today my Daddy, Ted Zellmer, went to heaven. 🕊 I will miss him but am so thankful I had all these years with him. What a gift. 🎁 During his life he raised lIvestock🐷, crops🌽, a church, and 2 daughters who love God, love others, and love our country. 🇺🇸 What a #blessing.🙏🏻 pic.twitter.com/XXlzhGz0Qk

After months of working with fellow conferees on behalf of rural America, I am proud to sign the #2018FarmBill and provide much needed certainty for producers and consumers both in Missouri and across our nation. pic.twitter.com/vfsSh3NOLY

Pleased the House voted last night to make common-sense reforms for our nation's veterans and servicemembers, S. 2248, the Veterans Benefit and Transition Act of 2018. We need to strengthen the way we care for those who have served and those who still serve our country today.

Pleased to announce that @POTUS signed into law the bill I authored to rename the downtown Columbia Post Office in honor of MO fallen soldier Spc. Sterling Wyatt. Sterling’s service to his country set an amazing example to the rest of our nation, and he is worthy of this honor. pic.twitter.com/rWxCV28Vji

(2/2) America has lost a true statesman. My thoughts and prayers are with the Bush family at this time.

(1/2) I was saddened to learn of the news that President George H.W. Bush had passed. “Bush 41,” as he was affectionately known, served his country in WWII as a combat pilot, then as an envoy to China, U.S. Representative, CIA Director, VP, and finally President of the U.S.
